. . . . Intriguing."—Harris Collingwood, Working Women "A wake-up call regarding the inequalities of an archaic system that actually penalizes women for working."—Publishers Weekly  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  agender, bias, discrimination, taxation, economy, finance, married filing joint, income taxes, dual-income household, family, legislation, economics, history, nonfiction, social security, working women, dink, marriage penalty, irs, 1040, wages, federal tax laws, contract with america, child-care expenses, second earner, marginal rates.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226555560423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226555560/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles